Limpopo police have welcomed the heavy sentences recently handed down to several criminals who are terrorising our peace loving citizens on their evil and sensless acts . William Mashai, 54, of Thapane village in Bolobedu South near Tzaneen was sentenced in the Polokwane High Court on Friday to two terms of life imprisonment for murder, Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said. This sentence was the result of an incident on September 11, 2015 at about 9pm, when Mashai drove to La Gratitude farm in the Letsitele policing area outside Tzaneen. On arrival he found his girlfriend Tsakane Ngobeni aged 42 together with Simon Baloyi aged 53, both from Mamitwa village, sleeping in her compound and he tied the door outside and poured this room with petrol and set it alight killing both instantly and fled the scene until he was later arrested at his house in Bolobedu South, Ngoepe said. This was the latest in a series of lengthy jail sentences handed down in the past 14 days. Kennith Magway, 30, was handed four life imprisonment terms for 11 counts of rape, and Katlego Gilbert Mphahlele, 29, was sentenced to life imprisonment for murder and four years imprisonment for theft A 28-year-old man was sentenced to life imprisonment for raping a young girl, and Frank Makgoka Thoka, 30, was sentenced to a total of 238 years imprisonment for 36 counts of violent crime, including rape, sexual assault, and robbery with aggravating circumstances. ALSO READ: DA condemns brutal farm attack in Gauteng This is another milestone achieved by the police in this province in their endeavours to fight crime effectively and members of the community are still encouraged to continuously support the police with quality and reliable information in the name of partnership policing, Ngoepe said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.